# Accepted-risk waivers for the Trivy CI gate (apps/*/Dockerfile image scans).
#
# Rules for this file:
#   - Every entry MUST have a reason AND a revisit condition.
#   - Only waive what is genuinely not fixable today. Prefer fixing.
#   - Keep it short. Re-check on each dependency-update sweep.

# CVE-2026-42504 — Go stdlib MIME-header DoS, compiled into the Caddy binary
# that ships in caddy:2-alpine (built with Go 1.26.3; the fix is Go 1.26.4).
#
# Why waived: we do not compile Caddy ourselves, and as of 2026-06-15 the
# newest published image (caddy:2.11.4 / the floating 2-alpine tag) is still
# built on Go 1.26.3 — there is no patched Caddy image to upgrade to. The
# finding is a denial-of-service (not RCE), and the edge sits behind Cloudflare.
#
# Revisit: the Dockerfile uses the floating `caddy:2-alpine` tag, so CI will
# pull the rebuilt image automatically once Caddy republishes on Go 1.26.4+.
# REMOVE this line then (the CVE will simply stop appearing).
CVE-2026-42504
